Privacy Policy

Protecting your private informtion is our priority. This Statement of Privacy applies to skynetgames.net and Skynet Games along
with any subsidary companies and websites and governs data collection and usage. For teh purposes of this Privacy Policy, unless
otherwise noted, all reference to Skynet Games include skynetgames.net and Skynet. By using the site you consent to the data
practices described in this statement. 

<Collection of your Personal Information>
If you donate to Skynet, we collect billing information in the form of the customers public bitcoin wallet. This information is
used to complete the transaction. The transaction is provided through a third party with no relation to Skynet.
We are required to collect certain pieces of information such as IP Address, Operating System, Nation, Device Type, HTTP/HTTPS. 
No other information will be collected unless you voluntarily provide it to us and the information automatically collected will
not be sold, rented, or leased to third parties. 
Data may be shared with trusted partners to help perform statistial analysis.

<External Data Storage Sites>
We may store your data on servers provided by third party hosting vendors with whom we have contracted. 

<Changes to Terms>
Skynet reserves the right, in its sole discretion, to change the Terms under which skynetgames.net is offered. The most current version
of the Terms will supersede all previous versions. Skynet encourages you to periodically review the Terms to stay informed of our updates. 

These terms and conditions are updated as of November 4, 2017 and website version #110517
